1
00:00:13,360 --> 00:00:14,760
Wenxin.

2
00:00:14,960 --> 00:00:15,600
Are you there?

3
00:00:15,600 --> 00:00:16,320
I'm here.

4
00:00:17,080 --> 00:00:19,520
Thank you for saving my daughter and me.

5
00:00:22,560 --> 00:00:23,490
You're welcome.

6
00:00:24,160 --> 00:00:25,820
You saved my life before, too.

7
00:00:25,840 --> 00:00:26,760
So,

8
00:00:28,240 --> 00:00:30,570
that car accident really was an accident.

9
00:00:30,920 --> 00:00:32,720
If it weren't for that accident,

10
00:00:33,360 --> 00:00:34,800
I would be the one dead.

11
00:00:35,360 --> 00:00:36,820
Drugging me at the picnic,

12
00:00:37,000 --> 00:00:38,400
pushing me into the water...

13
00:00:38,400 --> 00:00:40,320
The person I loved for ten years

14
00:00:41,280 --> 00:00:42,340
actually did this.

15
00:00:43,040 --> 00:00:45,300
No wonder people say the truth is brutal.

16
00:00:45,920 --> 00:00:47,850
But I'm glad I got my daughter back.

17
00:00:48,520 --> 00:00:50,560
If changing fate requires a price,

18
00:00:51,000 --> 00:00:52,160
to save my daughter,

19
00:00:52,640 --> 00:00:54,200
even if it costs my life,

20
00:00:55,000 --> 00:00:55,880
I am willing.

21
00:00:59,480 --> 00:01:01,400
Okay. Anyway,

22
00:01:01,760 --> 00:01:03,400
we survived today.

23
00:01:03,680 --> 00:01:04,959
That calls for a celebration.

24
00:01:04,959 --> 00:01:05,600
Yeah.

25
00:01:06,560 --> 00:01:07,560
But it's a pity.

26
00:01:08,120 --> 00:01:09,680
We are twelve days apart.

27
00:01:10,120 --> 00:01:12,120
If we were in the same time and space,

28
00:01:12,640 --> 00:01:15,160
I'd really love to have a drink with you

29
00:01:16,720 --> 00:01:17,780
and chat all night.

30
00:01:21,360 --> 00:01:23,320
Can you see the moon if you look up?

31
00:01:28,640 --> 00:01:29,320
Yes, I can.

32
00:01:29,600 --> 00:01:30,320
I can too.

33
00:01:39,640 --> 00:01:40,560
In a way,

34
00:01:41,800 --> 00:01:42,960
we are together.

35
00:01:45,200 --> 00:01:46,360
Let's celebrate.

36
00:01:53,640 --> 00:01:54,570
Do you regret it?

37
00:01:54,720 --> 00:01:55,720
I feel fortunate.

38
00:01:56,120 --> 00:01:57,240
Do you feel fortunate?

39
00:01:57,240 --> 00:01:58,360
I am worried.

40
00:01:58,800 --> 00:01:59,729
Are you worried?

41
00:02:00,200 --> 00:02:01,240
I am happy.

42
00:02:01,880 --> 00:02:02,760
Are you happy?

43
00:02:03,200 --> 00:02:04,200
I have no regrets.

44
00:02:54,680 --> 00:02:57,120
Didn't you say the plan was foolproof?

45
00:02:57,560 --> 00:03:00,490
Why is your wife still sitting safe and sound at home?

46
00:03:01,560 --> 00:03:03,360
Who knew some guy would show up out of nowhere?

47
00:03:03,360 --> 00:03:05,400
He saved her and ruined my plan.

48
00:03:07,560 --> 00:03:09,440
We have to strike while the iron is hot.

49
00:03:09,440 --> 00:03:11,360
Instead of waiting for her to realize something's wrong,

50
00:03:11,360 --> 00:03:13,360
we should act again right now.

51
00:03:15,560 --> 00:03:19,280
The company's debt won't wait for your slow planning.

52
00:03:20,920 --> 00:03:21,720
Got it.

53
00:03:24,480 --> 00:03:26,740
She doesn't suspect anything, does she?

54
00:03:31,440 --> 00:03:34,320
No. Don't worry.

55
00:05:59,040 --> 00:05:59,840
Honey.

56
00:06:02,600 --> 00:06:03,920
I thought you weren't home.

57
00:06:03,920 --> 00:06:05,180
Where else should I be?

58
00:06:12,080 --> 00:06:12,880
Honey.

59
00:06:19,760 --> 00:06:22,020
You haven't changed into your slippers.

60
00:06:47,560 --> 00:06:50,040
Honey, let me go change.

61
00:06:50,360 --> 00:06:51,490
I'm covered in dust.

62
00:06:51,680 --> 00:06:53,159
Okay, I'll start cooking.

63
00:06:53,560 --> 00:06:54,360
Okay.

64
00:07:38,680 --> 00:07:39,360
Honey.

65
00:07:40,159 --> 00:07:41,520
You changed so fast.

66
00:07:42,080 --> 00:07:42,680
Let's eat.

67
00:07:49,000 --> 00:07:50,400
Thanks for the hard work.

68
00:08:03,720 --> 00:08:04,720
Dinner is served.

69
00:08:08,960 --> 00:08:09,680
Try it.

70
00:08:19,040 --> 00:08:19,840
Who is it?

71
00:08:25,160 --> 00:08:25,960
Who is it?

72
00:08:29,880 --> 00:08:32,140
Is there something wrong with Chen Jian?

73
00:08:34,120 --> 00:08:35,240
So,

74
00:08:35,559 --> 00:08:36,919
he deleted them first.

75
00:08:38,280 --> 00:08:40,799
It's precisely because there are no records left

76
00:08:40,799 --> 00:08:42,059
that it's suspicious.

77
00:08:46,240 --> 00:08:48,400
I think for some things,

78
00:08:49,160 --> 00:08:51,020
you can find the answer yourself.

79
00:08:57,240 --> 00:08:57,720
Wenxin.

80
00:08:58,360 --> 00:08:59,160
I'm here.

81
00:08:59,760 --> 00:09:01,600
Wenxin is here too.

82
00:09:04,000 --> 00:09:04,800
Wenxin,

83
00:09:05,520 --> 00:09:06,600
are you okay?

84
00:09:08,440 --> 00:09:09,760
I'm fine.

85
00:09:10,280 --> 00:09:11,600
Sun Wen saved me.

86
00:09:12,000 --> 00:09:13,120
He saved us.

87
00:09:13,960 --> 00:09:15,040
I never thought

88
00:09:15,040 --> 00:09:16,720
I'd talk to myself like this.

89
00:09:17,000 --> 00:09:18,320
But we only have a minute.

90
00:09:18,320 --> 00:09:20,160
So listen to what I have to say.

91
00:09:21,600 --> 00:09:22,080
Okay.

92
00:09:22,080 --> 00:09:24,040
Chen Jian's company has a deficit.

93
00:09:24,160 --> 00:09:25,360
We can't trust him.

94
00:09:26,200 --> 00:09:27,000
Also,

95
00:09:27,800 --> 00:09:29,960
Sun Wen died once to save us.

96
00:09:30,960 --> 00:09:33,120
He's the most trustworthy person right now.

97
00:09:33,120 --> 00:09:33,920
Only him.

98
00:09:46,960 --> 00:09:48,560
Everything you said is true.

99
00:10:00,640 --> 00:10:03,000
Did she have something else to say just now?

100
00:10:03,000 --> 00:10:03,930
There are things

101
00:10:06,200 --> 00:10:08,200
I only told the you from twelve days later.

102
00:10:08,200 --> 00:10:11,060
If the me from twelve days later won't let you say it,

103
00:10:11,920 --> 00:10:13,050
then the me right now

104
00:10:13,240 --> 00:10:14,680
is asking you to tell me the truth.

105
00:10:14,680 --> 00:10:15,480
Are you sure?

106
00:10:21,680 --> 00:10:22,940
Chen Jian is cheating.

107
00:10:23,040 --> 00:10:25,960
He teamed up with Strawberry Meow Meow to kill you

108
00:10:26,720 --> 00:10:28,520
and get the compensation money.

109
00:10:31,680 --> 00:10:33,140
Let me show you something.

110
00:10:38,160 --> 00:10:40,160
Look. The you from twelve days later

111
00:10:40,240 --> 00:10:42,770
changed my destiny with this lottery ticket.

112
00:10:44,360 --> 00:10:47,320
I even paid for it with my life.

113
00:10:47,680 --> 00:10:48,400
Now,

114
00:10:50,000 --> 00:10:51,400
do you regret saving him?

115
00:10:57,160 --> 00:10:58,160
I don't regret it.

116
00:10:59,600 --> 00:11:02,160
Changing destiny comes with a price.

117
00:11:05,040 --> 00:11:06,960
Just like what the you from twelve days later said.

118
00:11:06,960 --> 00:11:08,220
Being able to save Xixi

119
00:11:08,560 --> 00:11:10,290
is something I'm grateful for.

120
00:11:11,480 --> 00:11:12,800
But now Chen Jian's company

121
00:11:12,800 --> 00:11:14,400
has a financial hole to fill.

122
00:11:15,320 --> 00:11:17,240
I'm afraid since he failed to kill you this time,

123
00:11:17,240 --> 00:11:18,970
he definitely has other plans.

124
00:11:19,240 --> 00:11:20,100
What about you?

125
00:11:20,720 --> 00:11:21,920
What do you plan to do?

126
00:11:23,920 --> 00:11:26,120
Instead of sitting here waiting to die,

127
00:11:27,080 --> 00:11:28,600
I'll take the initiative.
